---
description: Use Flutter Cockpit when a Flutter or host-control task needs live UI, route, screenshot, recording, or validation evidence.
globs:
  - "**/*.dart"
  - "pubspec.yaml"
  - "cockpit/**"
alwaysApply: false
---

Load the `flutter-cockpit` skill from `.cursor/skills/flutter-cockpit` before driving a Flutter app or claiming runtime validation. If skill discovery is unavailable, read `skills/flutter-cockpit/SKILL.md`.

Default to the smallest live loop:

```bash
dart run cockpit list-targets
dart run cockpit launch-app --project-dir <dir> --platform <platform> --device-id <id>
dart run cockpit read-app --profile minimal
dart run cockpit hot-reload
dart run cockpit capture-screenshot --name acceptance --profile inspect
```

Prefer `.cursor/mcp.json` or CLI through `dart run cockpit serve-mcp`. Do not treat command success as product proof; verify app state, errors, and evidence.
